rndMng.name: rndMng
rndMng.contactinfo: Postal: 170 West Tasman Drive San Jose , CA 95134-1706 USA Website: Cisco Small Business Home http://www.cisco.com/smb>;, Cisco Small Business Support Community <http://www.cisco.com/go/smallbizsupport>
rndMng.description: The private MIB module definition for switch001 general management MIB.

rndSysId.name: rndSysId
rndSysId.description: Identification of an switch001 device. The device type for each integer clarifies the sysObjectID in MIB - II.

rndAction.name: rndAction
rndAction.description: This variable enables the operator to perform one of the specified actions on the tables maintained by the network device. Send actions require support of proprietery File exchange protocol.

rndFileName.name: rndFileName
rndFileName.description: The name of the file used internally by switch001 for transferring tables maintained by network devices, using a prorietary File exchange protocol.

rlSnmpVersionSupported.name: rlSnmpVersionSupported
rlSnmpVersionSupported.description: Indicates the snmp versions that are supported by this device.

rlSnmpMibVersion.name: rlSnmpMibVersion
rlSnmpMibVersion.description: Indicates the snmp support version that is supported by this device.

rlCpuUtilEnable.name: rlCpuUtilEnable
rlCpuUtilEnable.description: Enables measurement of the device CPU utilization. In order to get real values for rlCpuUtilDuringLastSecond, rlCpuUtilDuringLastMinute and rlCpuUtilDuringLast5Minutes, the value of this object must be true.

rlCpuUtilDuringLastSecond.name: rlCpuUtilDuringLastSecond
rlCpuUtilDuringLastSecond.description: Percentage of the device CPU utilization during last second. The value 101 is a dummy value, indicating that the CPU utilization was not measured (since measurement is disabled or was disabled during last second).

rlCpuUtilDuringLastMinute.name: rlCpuUtilDuringLastMinute
rlCpuUtilDuringLastMinute.description: Percentage of the device CPU utilization during last minute. The value 101 is a dummy value, indicating that the CPU utilization was not measured (since measurement is disabled or was disabled during last minute).

rlCpuUtilDuringLast5Minutes.name: rlCpuUtilDuringLast5Minutes
rlCpuUtilDuringLast5Minutes.description: Percentage of the device CPU utilization during the last 5 minutes. The value 101 is a dummy value, indicating that the CPU utilization was not measured (since measurement is disabled or was disabled during last 5 minutes).

rlRebootDelay.name: rlRebootDelay
rlRebootDelay.description: Setting the variable will cause the device to reboot rlRebootDelay timeticks from the moment this variable was set. If not set, the variable will return a value of 4294967295. If set to 4294967295, reboot action is cancelled. The maximum delay is set by the host parameter: reboot_delay_max

rlGroupMngQuery.name: rlGroupMngQuery
rlGroupMngQuery.description: Setting value query will cause the device to query for UPNP devices on the network. The device will always return value idle for GET.

rlGroupMngQueryPeriod.name: rlGroupMngQueryPeriod
rlGroupMngQueryPeriod.description: Sets desired interval between queries for UPNP devices on the network. Setting 0 will result in no such query. Note that the actual query interval might be less than the set value if another application running in the device requested a shorter interval. Likewise setting 0 will not necessarily stop periodic queries if another application is still interested in periodic polling.

rlGroupMngLastUpdate.name: rlGroupMngLastUpdate
rlGroupMngLastUpdate.description: The last time rlGroupMng MIB was updated.

rlGroupMngDevicesTable.name: rlGroupMngDevicesTable
rlGroupMngDevicesTable.description: The table showing the discovered devices.

rlGroupMngDeviceEntry.name: rlGroupMngDeviceEntry
rlGroupMngDeviceEntry.description: The row definition for this table.

rlGroupMngDeviceIdType.name: rlGroupMngDeviceIdType
rlGroupMngDeviceIdType.description: The IP address type of the discovered device

rlGroupMngDeviceId.name: rlGroupMngDeviceId
rlGroupMngDeviceId.description: The IP address of the discovered device

rlGroupMngSubdevice.name: rlGroupMngSubdevice
rlGroupMngSubdevice.description: A subdevice within the rlGroupMngDeviceId. Only subdevices with greatest specifity will be kept (specific UUID device is more specific than basic device which is in turn more specific than root device.

rlGroupMngDeviceDescription.name: rlGroupMngDeviceDescription
rlGroupMngDeviceDescription.description: The discovery protocol description of the device.

rlGroupMngGroupMngEnabled.name: rlGroupMngGroupMngEnabled
rlGroupMngGroupMngEnabled.description: Indicates whether the device has Group Management enable.

rlGroupMngGroupLLDPDeviceId.name: rlGroupMngGroupLLDPDeviceId
rlGroupMngGroupLLDPDeviceId.description: The LLDP device id. If it is empty the device id is not known (either it is a non-MTS device or a non-LLDP supporting MTS device.

rlGroupMngDeviceVendor.name: rlGroupMngDeviceVendor
rlGroupMngDeviceVendor.description: The vendor of the device. If empty the vendor is not known.

rlGroupMngDeviceAdvertisedCachingTime.name: rlGroupMngDeviceAdvertisedCachingTime
rlGroupMngDeviceAdvertisedCachingTime.description: The caching time advertised by the device. If no update for this device has been received during this caching time the system will assume that the device has left the network and will therefore remove its entry from the table.

rlGroupMngDeviceLocationURL.name: rlGroupMngDeviceLocationURL
rlGroupMngDeviceLocationURL.description: The URL inidicating the location of the XML presenting the details of the device.

rlGroupMngDeviceLastSeen.name: rlGroupMngDeviceLastSeen
rlGroupMngDeviceLastSeen.description: The value of sysUpTime at the moment of last reception of an update for this device.

rlRunningCDBequalToStartupCDB.name: rlRunningCDBequalToStartupCDB
rlRunningCDBequalToStartupCDB.description: Indicates whether there are changes in running CDB that were not saved in flash.

rlClearMib.name: rlClearMib
rlClearMib.description: Clear MIB value for scalars or tables: Delete all entries for tables with dynamic entries. Set table entries default values for table with static entries. Set scalar default value.

rlScheduledReload.name: rlScheduledReload
rlScheduledReload.description: Used for requesting a delayed reload of the device in a specific desired time, should be configured in one of the following formats: 'athhmmddMM' , 'inhhhmmm' or '', setting this value to an empty string will result in request for cancellation of a (previously) committed system reload. to complete the request, the 'rlScheduledReloadCommit' must also be set to either TRUE (apply) or FALSE (discard) for completion of the transaction. failing from doing so will result in an indefinite lock of the API

rlScheduledReloadPendingDate.name: rlScheduledReloadPendingDate
rlScheduledReloadPendingDate.description: Displays the most recently requested scheduled-reload due date in 'inhhhmmathhmmssddMMYYYYw' format. where 'w' stands for weekDay (1-7). if there is no pending/scheduled reload request, string will be empty

rlScheduledReloadApprovedDate.name: rlScheduledReloadApprovedDate
rlScheduledReloadApprovedDate.description: Displays the most recently approved/committed scheduled-reload date in 'inhhhmmathhmmssddMMYYYYw' format. where 'w' stands for weekDay (1-7). if there is no committed scheduled-reload , string will be empty

rlScheduledReloadCommit.name: rlScheduledReloadCommit
rlScheduledReloadCommit.description: commits the pending scheduled-reload request, and completes the transaction. when this value is set to TRUE, the system is instructed to perform the requested reload operation at the requested date/time as was given in 'rlScheduledReload'. setting this value to FALSE will discard the request.

rlSysNameTable.name: rlSysNameTable
rlSysNameTable.description: Holds the current system name configuration.

rlSysNameEntry.name: rlSysNameEntry
rlSysNameEntry.description: The row definition of this table.

rlSysNameSource.name: rlSysNameSource
rlSysNameSource.description: The system name source. 'static' if defined by user through CLI, 'dhcpv6' or 'dhcpv4' if received by DHCP network protocol.

rlSysNameIfIndex.name: rlSysNameIfIndex
rlSysNameIfIndex.description: The IfIndex from which the system-name configuration was received, for static entries, value will always be 1.

rlSysNameName.name: rlSysNameName
rlSysNameName.description: An administratively-assigned name for this managed node. By convention, this is the node's fully-qualified domain name. If the name is unknown, the value is the zero-length string.

rlSysNameRowStatus.name: rlSysNameRowStatus
rlSysNameRowStatus.description: The row status variable, used according to row installation and removal conventions.
